  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Overview\r\nIt should be easy to skip a test unless a specific network is in use.\r\n\r\nhttps://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/88262/setup-brownie-to-run-certain-test-in-a-specific-network\r\n\r\n### Specification\r\nI'm not 100% on the best name, but I think a marker makes the most sense.  Something like this:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@pytest.mark.active_network('mainnet-fork')\r\ndef test_almost_in_prod():\r\n    ...\r\n```\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@pytest.mark.active_network('development')\r\ndef test_locally():\r\n    ...\r\n```\r\n",
